        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 7:16PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles north of Hermanas, moving southwest at 20 to 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hachita, Columbus, Carzalia Valley, Hermanas, Hachita Valley, Camp
Ramsey, and Waterloo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
